; the internal split-horizon zone for mesa.tetra.cool. a real zone file with derived addresses
; substituted by nix (replaceVars, see mesa-dns.nix): this resolver's own IP, the edge ingress
; VIP, and a block of one A record per fleet host at its own hostIp (fleet.topology's
; hostRecords). NOTE: replaceVars substitutes every literal occurrence of a placeholder token
; in this file, comments included -- don't write a placeholder's own at-sign-delimited name
; anywhere in prose, or it gets replaced too.
; the wildcard answers every other name under this zone from the edge VIP (fine for HTTP(S)
; vhosts); unifi and the per-host records are more-specific and win over it, no special-casing
; needed -- a direct-protocol hostname (SSH, Samba, NFS) needs its own record or it silently
; falls through to the edge VIP, which doesn't speak that protocol. serial is static (1) because
; this zone is generated, never hand-edited or transferred between servers.
$TTL 300
$ORIGIN mesa.tetra.cool.
@   IN SOA ns.mesa.tetra.cool. hostmaster.mesa.tetra.cool. (
        1          ; serial
        3600       ; refresh
        900        ; retry
        604800     ; expire
        300 )      ; negative cache ttl
    IN NS  ns.mesa.tetra.cool.
ns    IN A   @nsIp@
@     IN A   @edgeVip@
*     IN A   @edgeVip@
unifi IN A   192.168.1.1
@hostRecords@
